<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;">The Plugin Installation</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">You need to install the plugin name “ </span><span style="font-size: 15px; color: rgb(146, 146, 146); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.5;">View In Browser"</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Please read my notes on “Sublime 3 Installation and Plugins” how</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">to install the plugins.</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Note:</span> <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">To view a PHP code in the default browser</span></div><div>         <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147); font-weight: bold;">&lt;Control&gt;</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> + </span><span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147); font-weight: bold;">&lt;Option&gt;</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> + </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-weight: bold;">V</span></div><div>           <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">To run a PHP code in the console</span></div><div>         <span style="font-weight: bold;"> </span><span style="color: rgb(0, 143, 0); font-weight: bold;">&lt;Command&gt;</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> + </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-weight: bold;">B</span></div><div><br /></div><div>          - Open any valid PHP Project.</div><div>          - Make sure that you have your file inside that folder</div><div>          - Then open the file.</div><div>            </div><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">The Project Configuration</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 1</span>: <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Create a folder inside your root directory of your site:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">           # On my Mac OS the root directory of the website is</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">           # "/Users/khasanov/Sites “ and it can be accessed as</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">           # "</span><a href="http://localhost/~khasanov" style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">http://localhost/~khasanov</a><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">”</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">           # I will be creating the folder called “MyApp” inside my</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">           # site root folder :</span></div><div>           =&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">mkdir</span> <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">MyApp</span>  </div><div>           <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">#  /Users/khasanov/Sites/MyApp</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 2</span>: <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Open the Sublime and go to</span> “<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">Project</span>” -&gt; “<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">Save Project As …</span>”</div><div>            <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Give a name and save it inside the</span> “<span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">MyApp</span>”<span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"> folder</span>.</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 3</span>: <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Now we need to add our folder</span> “<span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">MyApp</span>” <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">to the project:</span></div><div>             <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Go to</span> “<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">Project</span>” <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">click on</span> “<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">Add Folder to Project..</span>” <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">and choose</span></div><div>            <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"> the project name you have created in Step 2.</span></div><div>             </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 4</span>: <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Go to</span> “<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">Project</span>”<span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"> and click on</span></div><div>             “<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">Edit Project</span>” <span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">and add the lines shown below:</span></div><div><hr /></div><div>   <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> {</span></div><div>   <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> "folders"</span>:</div><div>   <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> [</span></div><div>       <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);"> {</span></div><div>            "<span style="font-weight: bold;">path</span>": "<span style="font-weight: bold;">.</span>"</div><div>       <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);"> }</span></div><div>   <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> ]</span>,</div><div>    "<span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">settings</span>": <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">{</span></div><div>        "<span style="color: rgb(0, 143, 0);">sublime-view-in-browser</span>":<span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);"> {</span></div><div>            "<span style="font-weight: bold;">baseUrl</span>": "<a href="http://localhost/~khasanov/MyApp">http://localhost/~khasanov/MyApp</a>",</div><div>            "<span style="font-weight: bold;">basePath</span>": "<span style="color: rgb(148, 55, 255);">/Users/khasanov/Sites/MyApp</span>"</div><div>       <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);"> }</span></div><div> <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">   }</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">}</span></div><div><hr /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">Note: Edit the project file only with Sublime ( any other editor will cause you problem)</span></div><div><br /></div><div> </div><div><br /></div></en-note>